<p itemprop="description">A head of programme delivery is responsible for organisational programme delivery strategy and leads teams of programme managers. They work at executive level to drive delivery transformation, establish governance frameworks, and influence strategic direction.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Define and implement organisational programme delivery strategy</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead and manage teams of programme delivery managers</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Work with executive leadership on strategic transformation initiatives</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Establish programme governance and delivery frameworks</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Drive innovation and best practice in programme delivery</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Influence policy and strategic direction through delivery expertise</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Manage organisational delivery capability and transformation</li>
    </ul>
</section>

